{
  "texts": [
    "This confirms that BERT captures deeper linguistic patterns compared to static word embeddings.",
    "Eliminating category and subcategory embeddings also results in notable performance degradation.",
    "The decrease in AUC (by 1.7-2.5 points depending on whether BERT is used) suggests that these structured metadata features complement textual views by providing high-level semantic signals.",
    "This highlights the importance of integrating both unstructured and structured news information.",
    "Interestingly, the impact of removing word-level embeddings is even more pronounced in the non-BERT setting (drop from 0.6002 to 0.5650 in AUC), suggesting that without BERT, the model becomes more reliant on traditional word-level semantics."
  ]
}